transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, this is Vagra.

Speaker 2: Hello.

Speaker 1: Excuse me.

Speaker 2: Hello.

Speaker 1: How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yes, let me turn this on.

Speaker 1: Yeah, my name is Doug Lane, Douglas Lane.

Speaker 2: And what information do you need to pull up my file?

Speaker 1: I was able to pull your file here.

Speaker 2: I see that you have a prescription from Dr. Mayer for Vagra 100 milligrams,

Speaker 1: 10 tablets.

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Well, the reason I'm calling is I'm not using as many as I thought I was going to be using,

Speaker 1: and I need to cancel that prescription for a few months.

Speaker 2: Can you help me with that?

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: So I can pause it for half a year if you want, and that way you're on the monthly,

Speaker 1: and you can get it once or twice a year maybe.

Speaker 2: Yeah, right, because I think I got enough for about another six months.

Speaker 1: So just go ahead and put me on a list for another six months.

Speaker 2: Can you call me before you send it?

Speaker 1: Usually they send like a quick e-mail, but I'm having you for July 21st,

Speaker 2: if at least you know the date.

Speaker 1: Okay, so I can call back before then if I want to put it off a little bit longer.

Speaker 2: Okay, that's fine.

Speaker 1: I'll just go ahead and note it on my calendar that I need to call back about that.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Well, just go ahead and cancel that for six months from now.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: So you can reorder at the same price six months from now,

Speaker 2: but you're not going to get it every month, okay?

Speaker 1: That's great.

Speaker 2: Okay, thank you.

Speaker 1: See you all soon.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.

Speaker 1: All right, have a good one.

Speaker 2: You too.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.
